1.Git & GitHub Hands-on Experience (2026-03-03)✅

Today, I successfully established the complete workflow from my local development environment to a remote repository. This marks the technical foundation of my journey towards “GSoC 2027”.

💻Git Commands Executed
- `git init`: Initialized the local repository to enable version tracking.
- `git remote add origin`: Established the "pipeline" to the remote server.
- `git add .` & `git commit`: Performed "staging" and "checkpointing" of code changes.
- `git push -u origin main`: Successfully deployed local progress to the global server.
- `git pull`: Synced remote updates back to my local workspace.

